args: No... Elisanne, no! I didn't want this!
Open your eyes, Elly! Open them!\n...NOOOOOOO!
Honey, I'm so PROUD of you! Look how\nyou struck down your friend there!\nYou really are a beast at heart.
THIS is why you framed me, Dorothy!
You inspired doubt in Elisanne and\ngoaded her into fighting me so I would\ndo your dirty work and kill her!
Well, sure—but I ALSO did it so you would\nrealize you belong back with us in the\nworld of long knives and short lives!

Honey, honey! You're mad, I get it.
But really, I just set the table here.
You—and you alone—are responsible
for the actions you took after that.
I mean, are you really going to go back\nto tousling some moppet's hair with the\nsame hands that took a friend's life?

Yes, my child. Yes. Take the sword which
so recently claimed your friend's blood and
wield it for the world. This is the finest
tribute you can pay the Grand Paladyn.
Thanks to you, I can now obtain the\nkey to perdition and use it to bring\npeace to all of our adherents.
I thought you meant to bring that\nabout through reconciliation with\nthe conservative faction!

Such was indeed my intention at first.
However, I realized it was pointless to
try and persuade those conservatives,
slaves to existing values that they are.

Thus, I have opted to change tack. Instead,
I would make known the truth of our world,
and in so doing upend their value system
from its very foundations.

All was done in service to true harmony.
However, even with the truth staring them
square in the face, I suppose there are
some who cannot surrender their values.

Those who go so far in their foolishness
are naught but dead weight to be cut away.
But strength is required to purge them—
strength like that wielded by an assassin.
Come back to us, honey bunny.\nWE'RE the ones who really need you!
Twice did Elisanne show me the way,\nand then my comrades at the Halidom\nhelped me forge a new life altogether.

My past may be drenched in blood,
but I walk alongside them now on a path
as bright as the sun. THIS is the life I
would choose for myself—not yours!
I never expected you of all people\nto be so lovey and gross, sweetie.\nIt is VERY disappointing.
I have a new request for you, Dorothy.\nThe fool before you is an obstacle to true\nharmony. Do purge her with all haste.
You heard the man, darling—time to\ndrown this place in a sea of red!
Hey, this is the first time we've fought!\nI bet you thought I'd be all weak and\npretty just because I'm so smart, huh?
Eee hee! Eeeeeee hee hee hee!
Aw, are you tired from your fight earlier?\nC'mon, honey, get that rear in gear and\nmake this FUN for me already!
It's true that you might be more than\nI can handle right now...
But you're not more than WE can handle.
Darnit, I KNEW you were tricksey!\nHow in the name of cake are YOU alive?\nI saw Alex cut you down!
Just a small bit of mummery to get you\nwhere we wanted you, I'm afraid.

I was convinced of Alex's innocence from
the moment I stepped foot in this place.
And that being so, I turned my focus on
the assassin who set me on this path.
I knew you would follow me to ensure\nthe deed was done, and so kept up the\nruse in order to lower your guard.
And I knew right away that Elisanne\nbelieved me, just as I knew that our\ncrossing blades was mere show.
Okay, time the heck out! There's no WAY\nthe two of you improvised all that based\non the vague little conversation you had!
Friends need little more than a vague\nconversation to know the truth.

AAAAARGH! I can't believe I was set up
by a couple of starry-eyed fools prattling
about ＂friendship＂ and ＂love＂ and...and...
Oooo, it makes me wanna PUKE!
This is not gonna happen!\nI'M the one who laughs at the end!\nMe! Dorothy! MEEEEEE!
I AM NOT GONNA BE TRICKED BY A\nCOUPLE OF DO-GOODER CHUMPS!
You may have sent me packing today,\nbut this is NOT over!

I'm gonna smoosh this ＂friendship＂ of
yours until frosting squirts everywhere,
and I'm gonna laugh in your faces while
I do it!
Let her go. We've a more important\nmatter to deal with at the moment.
I heard everything, Archbishop Magnus,\nand now you will accept the judgment\nyou so richly deserve.
I will allow myself to be apprehended,\nbut do not think this means I have\nresigned myself to failure.
For I—and I alone—am the agent\nof the great will...
I got you a flower, Miss Elly!
I have returned to the daily life I desire.
You have been cleared of all charges.\nThere is no need to worry further.
Still, I wonder about the key to perdition\nthe archbishop spoke of, and how it\nconnects to the attempt on my life.
Yes, it's so very strange... Er, and speaking\nof things I do not understand, there's one\nother matter I wished to ask about.
How could you be so certain?\nAbout my innocence, I mean.\nYou seemed to know immediately.
You said your white hood was proof of\nthe vow you swore to never again be\nstained by blood, did you not?
Hey, there's prettier flowers over there!\nLet's go pick 'em together!
We should have a contest to see who\ncan pick the most. On your mark...\nGet set... GO!
Goddess willing, this happiness\nwill continue forever.
Forgive me for interrupting\nyour outing, Alex.
You were one of the knights pursuing me.
I was—and I wish to apologize for my\nrudeness the other day. But further,\nI've a matter I want to notify you of.
During questioning, the former\nArchbishop Magnus took his own life.
He was found stabbed in a room that \nwas locked from the inside. It is the\nonly possible explanation.

We had hoped to question him in regards
to the key to perdition, but now it seems
that truth will remain ever shrouded in
the gloom of darkness.
This was no suicide—it was the work\nof the director silencing a loose end.
...Nothing. Thank you for telling me this.\nI will go and inform Elisanne at once.

The old librarian said as much: So long
as there are those who covet the rest of
the Scrolls of Perdition, Elisanne's life
will be in terrible danger.
But no matter how thorny the path...
